==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Laid
<hw>Laid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <def>of
<er>Lay</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Laid paper</b></col>, <cd>paper marked with parallel
lines or water marks, as if ribbed, from parallel wires in the mold. It
is called <xex>blue laid</xex>, <xex>cream laid</xex>, etc., according
to its color.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laidly</ent>⟦br⟧
